spanishExample: ¡Encuentra la ropa verde!
englishTranslation: Find the green clothes!

spanishExample: ¡Entra por la puerta blanca!
englishTranslation: Go in through the white door!

spanishExample: ¡Mata al verde!
englishTranslation: Kill the green one!

spanishExample: ¿Encontraste a mi novio? Entramos en la casa, pero no sé dónde está.
englishTranslation: Did you find my boyfriend? We entered the house, but I don’t know where he is.

spanishExample: ¿Recuerdas cuando teníamos treinta y dos años?
englishTranslation: Do you remember when we were thirty-two?

spanishExample: A mi marido no le gusta matar.
englishTranslation: My husband doesn’t like killing.

spanishExample: Creo que ella no recuerda cómo encontrar las rojas.
englishTranslation: I think she doesn’t remember how to find the red ones (f).

spanishExample: Cuando entren, habrá treinta y una o treinta y cuatro personas.
englishTranslation: When they enter, there will be either thirty-one or thirty-four people.

spanishExample: Encontramos los azules, pero no los rojos.
englishTranslation: We found the blue ones, but not the red ones.

spanishExample: Encontraron treinta y seis perros negros ahí.
englishTranslation: They found thirty-six black dogs there.

spanishExample: Entramos en una casa con treinta y siete puertas azules.
englishTranslation: We’re entering a house with thirty-seven blue doors.

spanishExample: Entró por la puerta roja.
englishTranslation: He came in through the red door.

spanishExample: Hay treinta y nueve humanos ahí, y treinta y ocho perros.
englishTranslation: There are thirty-nine humans there, and thirty-eight dogs.

spanishExample: He encontrado treinta y uno.
englishTranslation: I have found thirty-one.

spanishExample: Las verdes van a matarme, pero las blancas están bien.
englishTranslation: The green ones (f) are going to kill me, but the white ones (f) are fine.

spanishExample: Mi abuelo tiene un auto rojo y está entrando en la casa.
englishTranslation: My grandfather has a red car and he’s entering the house.

spanishExample: No he matado treinta y uno, he matado treinta y tres.
englishTranslation: I haven’t killed thirty-one, I’ve killed thirty-three.

spanishExample: No mata nada.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t kill anything.

spanishExample: No pudimos entrar, pero encontramos a su novia afuera.
englishTranslation: We couldn’t enter, but we found his girlfriend outside.

spanishExample: Quiero que recuerde que mi abuela no es una idiota.
englishTranslation: I want him to remember that my grandmother is not an idiot.

spanishExample: Si no encuentras las treinta y cinco cosas, será un problema.
englishTranslation: If you don’t find the thirty-five things, it’ll be a problem.

spanishExample: Tienes que recordar que lo mataste.
englishTranslation: You have to remember that you killed it.
